Step0:   Connect DUT and Reboot HostPlatform
Step1:   Put new image to ./cascade.bin
Step2:   $ source env.sh
		 And then select (x86_64) or (aarch64) environment 
Step3:   $ ./update_image.sh

Option: tool to read firmware version
         $ ./read_fwver
               or
         $ ./read_fwver -f filepath

Option: tool to check chip-version
         $ sudo ./check_version -h
        To dump HELP menu

TroubleShooting:
1. If crc32 not found, please try:
   $ sudo apt-get install libarchive-zip-perl
2. If libpci.so not found, please try:
   $ sudo apt-get install libpci-dev
   
   
   
   
